result.name: Mirch Masala

reviews.text:
Located few km away from ocean park,  on 1st floor at Stanley plaza. Basically adjacent to Stanley market. 
Quite spacious place,  nice humble host,  with a good bar . They have set of meal too,  which is really pocket friendly. 
Serving vise,  they served the drinks,  then starters. Being a good host, the moment we finished the starters,  the main menu was served.,which was impressive.  
Quick service. 
Taste- average to good.  Overall good. 
Must visit though.
The food was delicious and the staff very friendly. Will definitely go again
the food here was tasteful and delicious; spices could be moderated up to your personal choice. Amazing service, great for any first timer trying out Indian food! Would definitely visit again!

Very good Indian restaurant at stanley. With traditional cuisine and spicy food which can custom the spaciness.

The service is great.
The food was OK, but the service is miserable and aggressive, fully depend what you order. The portion is very small compare the price.

result.adr_address: 23 Carmel Rd, Stanley, Hong Kong
result.name: Stanley Plaza

reviews.text: Some great shops here. Especially like A station, they have a wide range of gifts for all. Staff are friendly. Worth a visit.

Meeeh.. great location and beautiful sea views. However the plaza lacks focus. The choice of shops and restaurants doesn’t really appeal for tourists nor locals. For me it lacks a good business strategy.
The view is fantastic. Staff are friendly and nice. Coffee is good and cake is delicious.

Beautiful place, bought something from the market place, toy stores are quite pricey and some stores are have very good deals. 
I'll give 3 stars for the market place. And 5 stars for the food and views there. Beautiful, just wish I have more time to stay
A wonderful location to sit and relax, some casual shopping or to have a bite to eat... expect to spend the whole day here and enjoy it!
